{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012EAJWFkq9f6DrWd6nb2KHC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"After reviewing the code, I realize true streaming is a deep architectural change — the DSP operations (STFT, spectral cleaning, fingerprint removal) all work on the entire buffer at once. Chunked processing with proper overlap-add for STFT would require significant refactoring of every sanitization module.\n\nA practical approach for this issue: **Add a chunked processing mode to the pipeline** that splits large files into overlapping segments, processes each independently, and crossfades them back together. This handles the OOM concern without rewriting every DSP module.\n\nLet me implement this:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2447,"cache_read_input_tokens":108591,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2447},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9bd7957-c8f2-4e48-8fcc-7059d242854c","uuid":"fab5f56b-a7d4-4eb1-b235-cfbc1a19c637"}
